<p>In Suru Kavian dialect, vowels in certain directly possessed nouns and possessive classifiers change according to the pattern illustrated below. This does not occur in other dialects:</p>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<td>1st person singular</td>
<td><i>n<b>o</b>ngg<b>o</b> bu</i><br />
